      "summary": "Effect of fine-tuning on adversarial examples (ResNet-18/CIFAR-10, 10% forget). Across all three sub-figures (using D∪D_A, D_F∪D_A, D_A respectively), the 'Adv' curve maintains test accuracy above 80% through 20 epochs (specifically 80-90% range). In contrast, Adv-RS, Adv-RL, Orig-RL, Orig-AdvL curves all collapse to under 50% test accuracy by epoch 5 and stay there. This demonstrates that fine-tuning on adversarial examples does NOT cause catastrophic forgetting of test accuracy.",
